{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιφαίνω</b>, <br /> <i>aorist</i> I (late) <b>-έφᾱνα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Deu.33.2, NT.Luke.1.79 \">LXX+NT</a>]:—<b>show forth, display,</b> <i>absolutely</i>, μηδὲ λίην ἐπίφαινε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 359 (assuming variant); ἐ.προστασίαν ἀξιωματικήν 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.18.8; μηδὲν τεχνικόν 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “Amm.” 1.10 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ ἀγέρωχον, τὴν προαίρεσιν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marcellus” 1, 2.139d; ἀνθρωπόμορφόν τι 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 12 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; τὸν μισοπόνηρον <b>play</b> the μ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.74 W\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>].:—<i>passive</i>, <b>come into view,</b> ἠέλιος δ᾽ ἐπέλαμψε, μάχη δ᾽ ἐπὶ πᾶσα φαάνθη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.650 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of an enemy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.152, 4.122, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.42, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; διὰ τὸ ἐπιφανέντα με κωλῦσαι Test. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.22; ἐ.ἐς τὴν Νάξον 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.30, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.13; ἐπιφανῆναι ἐπὶ τὸ ἔργον [prev. author] “Oec.” 21.10; ἐπὶ τὰ Δρέπανα 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.49.7; ἐ.τινὶ ἐς οἶκον \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>to present oneself,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.97 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. τινί <b>show oneself, appear</b> to one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.24, +others\">Refs</a>]; frequently of dreams and visions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.91, 3.27; ἐν τῷ ὕπνῳ [prev. author] 7.16 \">Refs</a>]; of a divine manifestation, ἐπιφαινομένης αὐτοῖς Ἀρτέμιδος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 557.5 (Magn.Mae., 3rd c.BC),compare “IG” 4.951.26 (Epid., 3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; so ἡ χρηστότης ἐπεφάνη τοῦ θεοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Tit.3.4 \">NT</a>]; of an Emperor, δήμοις ἑορτάζουσιν ἐπιφανείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 1.7.2; also ἵνα σφι τιμωρίη..ἐπιφανήσεται 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.49; τὰ ἐπιφαινόμενα \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>symptoms which make their appearance,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 1.12, compare 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.17, +others \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> c.<i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, <b>make it manifest that..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1044d. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, literal <b>appear upon the surface,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 101d; ἐ. ταῖς εἰκόσιν ἰδέα 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Aratus” 3: _metaphorically_, τὸ ἦθος ὡς χρῶμα ταῖς πράξεσιν ἐ. [prev. work] 48,compare “Galb.” 23. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> seemingly <i>intransitive</i>, in <i>active</i>, <b>show light, dawn,</b> ἡμέρας ἐπιφαινούσης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.6.6 (so ἀνατολῆς ἐπιφαινομένης [prev. author] 3.113.1); ἐπιφᾶναι τοῖς ἐν σκότει καθημένοις \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<b>to shine upon</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Luke.1.79, cf. LXX.Deu.33.2. \">LXX+NT</a>]","strongNumber":"G2014","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιφαίνω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1909","matchingForm":"ἐπί","stepTransliteration":"epi","gloss":"upon/to/against","_zh_tw_Gloss":"在","_es_Gloss":"sobre/a/contra ","_zh_Gloss":"在"},{